        "text": " in A.V. makes the sense clearer. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "They entered into Caesarea",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". A memorable event, being the first invasion of the Roman empire by the soldiers of the cross. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "His near friends",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". We have here a proof of the strong faith of Cornelius. He did not doubt the angel's promise (vers. 5 and 6). We see his brotherly love. He invited his friends to come and hear the message of salvation; those whom, as Chrysostom suggests, he had himself brought to a better mind. Acts 10:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
